attributes.body: Pharmers Quality Concentrates is New Mexicos premier manufacture of high-end concentrates. We are the chemistry focused cannabis extraction laboratory in Socorro, New Mexico. We strive to provide the highest quality cannabis oil available by imploring the use of modern organic chemistry. We specialize in cannabinoid extraction, distillation, isolation, and remediation of contaminants. We believe it is important to trust the source of your medicine. Along time ago before marijuana prohibition, people were able to purchase Cannabis Oil at Pharmacies across the country. These pharmacies sold classily, trusted brands of medicine made by chemists with a true want to help and provide relief to their consumers. These brands were proud and stood by their medicine and so do we. Our motto is QUALITY COMES STANDARD because we believe it should! Our highly qualified staff of Laboratory Technicians will ensure that the utmost care is taken in the handling, extraction, and processing of your Cannabis oils. attributes.name: Forbidden Cake | Outdoor
attributes.body: Cross between Wedding Cake x Forbidden Fruit In 2015 we were shovel ready and applied but were denied licensure due to political shenanigans in Santa Fe. Unwilling to accept defeat or wait years to start this journey we are grateful that one badass company known as Urban Wellness with great forward thinking leaders gave us a chance to prove our concepts and build a track record of success working under their license. That lasted from 2016 though 2021 when we were awarded the first production license following the passage of the Cannabis Regulation Act. Getting our own license allowed us to scale our systems and grow our community. Today we work with 15 groups of contractors/people that make up the #LavaLeafCollective or #FarmFamily working on our property. We have also helped 4 family owned companies with similar values to obtain licensure and to get their cultivation operations off the ground. One major differentiator that we hope becomes the norm, is that we do not hire growers we partner with them. We believe that business owners will take more pride in and responsibility for their work. This means that more love and care is given to each nugget of flower Lava Leaf produces. New Mexico is home to many great producers so high quality is now par for the course. Now we are leveling up our systems and driving a conversation around equity and the sustainability of cannabis production. When purchasing cannabis we hope people will question, how was this grown? Was it a sustainable use of water and power? Does this company recycle? Are the growers or creators of this product valued?

attributes.name: Lemon Drip
attributes.body: Prohibition 37 flower is our specialty and what we have built our brand on. Our production facilities include 2 state-of-the-art indoor cultivations totaling 14,000 sq ft in our home city of Albuquerque. We also have an outdoor farm in Belen, and greenhouse productions in Belen and Gallup. Our mission is to destigmatize the industry, produce outstanding quality cannabis, and positively contribute to the quality of life of our patients and customers. We currently grow over 75 cultivars, and are continually adding the newest and most sought after genetics to bring to every corner of New Mexico. WHO IS P37? Prohibition 37 is a physician-led, nationally recognized, and award-winning vertical cannabis company. P37 is highly focused on the customer experience and science of the medicinal and recreational effects of its many products. Our name is derived from The Marihuana Tax Act of 1937, which was a U.S. federal law that effectively criminalized the possession and distribution of marijuana. While it did not directly ban the cannabis plant, it imposed strict regulations and heavy taxes on its cultivation, sales, and use. This made it impossible to legally engage in these activities, leading to a de facto prohibition of cannabis. The Act played a significant role in shaping the modern approach to marijuana regulation in the United States.\ SOCIAL EQUITY AND JUSTICE The Marihuana Tax Act of 1937 disproportionately targeted minorities, particularly African, Mexican, and Jewish American communities. While the act did not explicitly mention racial or ethnic groups, its implementation and enforcement were marked by tremendous racial bias and discrimination. Law enforcement, for example, selectively targeted and arrested individuals from minority groups and used marijuana-related offenses as a pretext for discriminatory actions. This contributed to the disproportionate impact of the Act on minorities, perpetuating racial stereotypes and injustices for generations to come. Our mission at Prohibition 37 is to reverse decades of cannabis-related injustice and create a healthy, communal, and scientific approach to cannabis use.

attributes.name: Frenchy Pebbles | Disposable
attributes.body: Live Extraction As opposed to drying and curing, the essence of the living cannabis plant is preserved through freezing immediately after harvest and remaining frozen throughout extraction. This process retains a broader spectrum of live terpenes and cannabinoids in higher volumes, yielding an exotic alternative to traditional BHO extracts. Live BHO typically resembles that of the plant in its final stage of flowering when terpene potency is at its peak generating robust aromatics and delivering unmatched piquancy. Adding enticing nuances to the typical cannabis extract palate, live extracts have become the first choice of the modern connoisseur. Traditional Extraction Utilizing dried and cured cannabis, this process extracts the cannabinoids, along with the aroma and flavor of the plant you love into a powerful concentrate. The best extracts of cannabis leave behind many of the carcinogenic substances the plants produce while preserving the desirable contents they contain. Cannabis extract can manifest a variety of dynamic textures, consistencies, and useful by-products such as H.T.S.F.E. Furthermore, cannabis extract has become the industrys preferred method for infusing activated cannabinoids, such as ?9-THC, into ingestible and topical products. Refined Extraction Take into consideration the environmental pollutants and agricultural contaminants that can be associated with cannabis cultivation, the subsequent extracts can contain unwanted impurities, pigments, and even harmful chemicals. Our proprietary filtration techniques and chromatography methodologies allow us to remediate compromised or otherwise undesirable extracts while maintaining the desirable components such as cannabinoids and terpenes. The end result meets all standards for consumption from shelf-ready solid extract to liquid and food-grade variations. By making these processes available, we aim to help eliminate large-scale waste associated with the ever-expanding industry of commercial cannabis.

attributes.name: Rihanna | Live Resin Wet Sugar
attributes.body: Here at Olio, we only use N-Butane for our solvent extractions, which we believe offers a more gentle extraction that results in more depth to the profile of our final concentrate. With our gardens focus on maximizing and preserving the resin production, we want to do everything in our power to make sure those same amazing aromas stay as true to nature all the way to the end. Wet Sugar: A form of Live Resin defined by the volume of terpenes present which typically falls in the 40% range. The extra terpenes offer more flavor and aroma but at the cost of a slightly harsher smoke. In theory, the additional terpenes should also enhance the psychoactive effects of the concentrate. More terpenes vaporized alongside the cannabinoids should engage more of an entourage effect.
